Always use type hints in Python functions
Always add docstrings to every function and class (Google style)
Use black formatting (88 char line length)
Use pathlib.Path instead of os.path
Log using Python logging module, never use print() in production code
Always handle exceptions with specific error types
Write modular, reusable functions — no monolithic scripts
Each .py file must have a if __name__ == "__main__": block
Use config files (YAML) for all hyperparameters, never hardcode values
